==English==

===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun|-}}

# Any of various political philosophies that support social and economic equality, collective decision-making{{,}} and public control of productive capital and natural resources, as advocated by [[socialist]]s.
# The socialist political philosophies as a group, including [[Marxism]], [[libertarian socialism]], [[democratic socialism]], and [[social democracy]].
# {{cattag|Leninism}} The intermediate phase of social development between [[capitalism]] and full [[communism]]. This is a strategy whereby the State has control of all key resource-producing industries and manages most aspects of the market, in contrast to [[laissez faire]] [[capitalism]].


